  "title": "Setting rootPath on HierarchicalMenu shows up in CurrentRefinements",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nSetting rootPath on HierarchicalMenu shows up in CurrentRefinements\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**\r\n\r\n1. See that rootPath is set on HierarchicalMenu\r\n2. Add another facet refinement by clicking a brand\r\n3. Click the clear refinements button\r\n4. See error, the rootPath now shows up in the CurrentRefinements and ClearRefinements widgets, and it's also showing in the URL.\r\n\r\n<!-- A live example helps a lot! Fork the sandbox, reproduce the bug and paste the URL here: -->\r\n\r\n**Live reproduction:**\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/wild-smoke-5m42st?file=/App.tsx\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nRefinement passed as rootPath to HierarchicalMenu should be invisible for the user. This is how it works in the non-hooks version.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- React InstantSearch Hooks version: 6.38.1\r\n",
